         <entry xml:id="Slips_SouthLochboisdaleJCampbellslips-idp115456152">
            <form>
               <orth>làthach</orth>
               <pron>[ɫɑ:hɑx]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[ɫɑ:hɑx] Notes: mud on the bottom of the sea or a loch.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_SouthLochboisdaleJCampbellslips-idp115475304">
            <form>
               <orth>osan</orth>
               <pron>[ɔsɑ̃ṉ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[ɔsɑ̃ṉ] Notes: (1) hole in lobster. (2) trouser leg.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_SouthLochboisdaleJCampbellslips-idp115473144">
            <form>
               <orth>poit</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: a’ poiteadh [pɔitʹəɣ]. Notes: used when talking about mending ragged old clothes; “patching up”.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_SouthLochboisdaleJCampbellslips-idp115468608">
            <form>
               <orth>cuaran</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: pl. [ku̜əɾɑ̃nʹ]. Notes: bandages on hands or feet. Also used of wrapping on hands when gutting herring.</def>
         </entry>
